FT  15 AUG 94 / Search for Guppy gems fraud money
The government has appointed Mr John Alexander, chairman of the corporate
recovery section at accountants Pannell Kerr Forster, to search for money
under the control of Mr Darius Guppy.
Mr Guppy was jailed for five in March last year after being convicted of a
Pounds 1.8m insurance fraud involving a bogus gems theft at a New York
hotel.
